<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News]]></title><link/> https://sputniknews.com/新闻<atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/sputniknews" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RSSHub</generator><webmaster> i@diygod.me (DIY神)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 5 月 25 日星期四 10:56:24 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[House Unveils Steps 'to Deter Invasion of Taiwan' as US-China Tensions Persist]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110579203" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107912/70/1079127059_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_fb8fdbdb620082a44fac0540628b8db3.jpg?source-sid=" data-photoview-image-id="1079127057" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230525/house-unveils-steps-to-deter-invasion-of-taiwan-as-us-china-tensions-persist-1110579203.html?share-img=1079127057"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://www.navy.mil/management/photodb/photos/230420-N-NK931-1001.JPG" title="士官二等 Jim Ong">二级军官 Jim Ong</a></span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">Arleigh-Burke 级导弹驱逐舰 USS Barry (DDG 52) 正在进行例行的正在进行的操作。 Barry 被前沿部署到美国第 7 舰队行动区，以支持印太地区的安全与稳定。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="" alt="The Arleigh-Burke class guided missile destroyer USS Barry (DDG 52) conducts routine underway operations. Barry is forward-deployed to the U.S. 7th Fleet area of operations in support of security and stability in the Indo-Pacific region. - Sputnik International, 1920, 25.05.2023" title="Arleigh-Burke 级导弹驱逐舰 USS Barry (DDG 52) 正在进行例行的在航行动。 Barry 被前沿部署到美国第七舰队行动区，以支持印太地区的安全与稳定。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107912/70/1079127059_0:160:3073:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_d3e7d67eae35b8b933df8ecae401e6ef.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107912/70/1079127059_0:160:3073:1888_640x0_80_0_0_e4b1f47e14151b9bcc2cc012afae9c84.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107912/70/1079127059_0:160:3073:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_e3f6b0f06830d706836b9229b9d3dcd9.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107912/70/1079127059_0:160:3073:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_d3e7d67eae35b8b933df8ecae401e6ef.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © <a href="https://www.navy.mil/management/photodb/photos/230420-N-NK931-1001.JPG" title="士官二等 Jim Ong">二级士官 Jim Ong</a> </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-image"><img media-type="s150x150" data-source-sid="not_sputnik_photo" alt="Oleg Burunov - Sputnik International" title="奥列格布鲁诺夫" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/09/0b/1080424846_0:0:2048:2048_100x100_80_0_0_3d7b461f8a98586fa3fe739930816aea.jpg" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">奥列格布鲁诺夫</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_burunov_oleg/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a> <a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:o.burunov@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">中国一再与美国在台湾问题上发生争执，北京认为台湾是中国的一部分，而华盛顿则向该岛投放越来越多的武器。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">众议院美中战略竞争特别委员会就如何“维护台海和平与稳定”提出了十项“政策建议”和提案。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在周三的一份报告中，共和党领导的小组表示希望将调查结果纳入 2024 财年国防授权法案 (NDAA)。众议院早些时候推迟了对 2024 NDAA 的审议，而国会则致力于解决<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230525/debt-ceiling-negotiators-relocated-to-white-house-to-hammer-out-deal-before-june-deadline-1110573400.html" target="_blank">美国债务</a>上限的僵局。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><em>报告警告说，如果不采取“紧急措施”，“美国可能无法阻止入侵台湾”，显然是在向中国点头。</em> </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p>北京认为台湾是中国的重要组成部分，反对台湾与其他国家进行任何官方接触，早些时候承诺推动台湾“和平统一”进程。中国国家主席习近平承诺，中国将着眼于“两岸关系和平发展”，抵制外来干涉和分裂主义。他此前曾保证，北京“坚定奉行独立与和平的外交政策”。</p></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该调查的建议包括<strong>增加对台北的关键弹药销售，</strong>以向人民解放军 (PLA) 展示“更具挑战性和复杂的威胁环境”，以及与盟国制定联合计划以促进与台湾的经济接触。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">此外，该小组还呼吁<strong>在台湾建立一个战争储备武器库</strong>，在整个印太地区加强和部署美国军队，以及扩大美国和台湾军队之间的训练和协调。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230506/us-to-reportedly-fast-track-500-mln-arms-for-taiwan-amid-narrative-of-china-threat-1110137406.html" target="_blank">华盛顿和台北就</a>美台 21 世纪贸易倡议的第一部分达成协议后将近一周，这些提议就出现了。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p>美国贸易代表凯瑟琳·泰上周告诉记者，该协议“代表着加强美台经济关系向前迈出的重要一步”。她补充说，这笔交易涵盖了海关和边境程序、监管实践和小企业。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110579203" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230525/house-unveils-steps-to-deter-invasion-of-taiwan-as-us-china-tensions-persist-1110579203.html?share-block=1110579211" data-title="US Trade Representative Katherine Tai told reporters last week that the agreement &amp;quot;represents an important step forward in strengthening the US-Taiwan economic relationship.&amp;quot; She added that the deal covers customs and border procedures, regulatory practices, and small business."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Tai 表示，在达成初步协议后，将就两国更复杂的贸易领域进行谈判，例如农业、数字贸易、劳工和环境标准，以及非市场政策和实践。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美国媒体援引亚洲协会政策研究所副总裁、前美国贸易谈判代表<em>温迪·卡特勒</em>的话说，“北京可能会抱怨这一声明，但随着谈判的继续，华盛顿将置若罔闻”与台湾。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p>时任美国众议院议长南希佩洛西于 2022 年 8 月初访问台湾后，北京和华盛顿之间因台湾问题持续紧张，事态发展。北京谴责佩洛西的访问，称其为支持分裂主义的姿态，并举行了大规模军事行动作为报复行动，在台湾附近演习。</p></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">尽管美国与台湾没有正式外交关系，但华盛顿在台北设有代表处，并且仍然是台湾最大的军事装备供应商。美国还经常派军舰和侦察机前往<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230428/chinese-air-forces-observe-us-military-aircraft-flying-over-taiwan-strait-1109913400.html" target="_blank">台湾海峡</a>，北京抨击此类任务是挑衅，并指出华盛顿不过是“该地区安全风险的制造者”。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 25 May 2023 10:46:05 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230525/house-unveils-steps-to-deter-invasion-of-taiwan-as-us-china-tensions-persist-1110579203.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230525/house-unveils-steps-to-deter-invasion-of-taiwan-as-us-china-tensions-persist-1110579203.html<category>世界</category><category>我们</category><category>中国</category><category>台湾</category><category>紧张局势</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Finland Gets Flak From European Commission for Skyrocketing Debt]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110577660" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/104948/62/1049486287_0:0:1280:828_1440x900_80_0_1_bee5879925cbd29ceb22724a737f4a8e.jpg?source-sid=not_sputnik_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1049486286" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230525/finland-gets-flak-from-european-commission-for-skyrocketing-debt-1110577660.html?share-img=1049486286"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© 照片：Pixabay /</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">欧元</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="not_sputnik_photo" alt="Euros - Sputnik International, 1920, 25.05.2023" title="欧元" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/104948/62/1049486287_0:54:1280:774_1920x0_80_0_0_a70322f4e7587d0eb9964062d5d1dc50.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/104948/62/1049486287_0:54:1280:774_640x0_80_0_0_7932be616cba0c9cd0c15226f2f8e1bd.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/104948/62/1049486287_0:54:1280:774_1280x0_80_0_0_b492af2218384c1fa199f1b0e5c573db.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/104948/62/1049486287_0:54:1280:774_1920x0_80_0_0_a70322f4e7587d0eb9964062d5d1dc50.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 照片：Pixabay / </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">伊戈尔·库兹涅佐夫</div><div class="article__author-links"> <a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_kuznetsov_igor/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">赫尔辛基的债务与 GDP 的比率自 00 年代以来一直在稳步上升。到 2022 年，芬兰将成为欧盟中唯一一个进一步增长的国家。随着该国进入衰退，债务问题给尚未组建的未来政府提出了额外的问题。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">芬兰不断膨胀的国债引发了欧盟委员会的反应，该委员会在其最近的报告中呼吁北欧国家迅速果断地解决这个问题。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><a href="https://sputniknews.com/tag_Finland/" target="_blank" data-auto="true">芬兰</a>前财政部长<a href="https://sputniknews.com/person_Petteri_Orpo/" target="_blank" data-auto="true">佩特里·奥尔波（Petteri Orpo）</a>表示，他领导着组建新芬兰政府的努力，自由保守党全国联合党的领导人表示，欧盟的研究清楚地表明，芬兰的债务占 GDP 的比例为 73%，比其北欧同行要可怕得多。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">他表示，他不想将芬兰与南欧国家进行比较，他认为，南欧国家对债务“传统上有不同的态度”，坚持认为芬兰应该与其他北欧国家和德国保持一致。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">去年，13 个成员国的公共债务超过了欧盟允许的限额。此外，其中三个国家——芬兰、法国和意大利——未能遵守欧盟内部商定的债务削减目标。值得注意的是，芬兰成为<strong>整个欧盟国家中去年公共财政债务比率上升的唯一国家</strong>。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">欧盟委员会负责经济事务的副主席<a href="https://sputniknews.com/tag_ValdisDombrovskis/" target="_blank" data-auto="true">瓦尔迪斯·东布罗夫斯基斯</a>表示，欧盟正在特别关注赤字超过 3% 或公共债务超过 60% 参考值的 16 个成员国。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Dombrovskis 还大胆指出，这些国家的<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230512/western-inflation-self-inflicted-problem-with-no-end-in-sight-1110269612.html" target="_blank">经济状况</a>不支持过度赤字程序，这意味着欧盟行政当局可能会命令成员国减少公共债务和赤字。如果不这样做，在最坏的情况下可能会招致进一步的罚款。在 COVID-19 危机和乌克兰冲突期间，欧盟成员国被允许有更多的喘息空间来偏离《稳定与增长公约》(SGP) 的一般规则。然而，更严格的措施可能会在 2024 年出台，届时欧盟有望恢复更为保守的经济管理。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">欧盟委员会就如何减少债务向芬兰发布了针对特定国家的提示，其中包括取消该国的<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230314/finns-forked-out-5bln-extra-in-power-costs-last-year-report-says-1108363240.html" target="_blank">巨额能源补贴</a>以节省公共财政，减少<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230515/somewhat-surprising-finnish-petrol-prices-soar-to-all-european-highs-1110361001.html" target="_blank">对化石燃料的依赖</a>并加快使用可再生能源以及纠正其劳动力和人才短缺问题。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Petteri Orpo 是<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230403/finland-facing-likely-rightward-turn-as-rock-star-pm-loses-election-1109061879.html" target="_blank">芬兰大选的获胜者</a>和<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230404/who-is-petteri-orpo-the-man-set-to-be-finlands-new-pm-1109098149.html" target="_blank">现任总理</a>，他是一位财政保守派，他承诺削减失业救济金和其他福利计划。他特别承诺减少公共债务，促进减税和促进经济增长。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">芬兰的债务占 GDP 的比率在 2008 年降至 34.7%（几十年来的最低点）后，在过去二十年一直稳步上升。随着国家进入<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230307/finnish-economy-enters-technical-recession-amid-inflation-spike-1108135810.html" target="_blank">技术性衰退</a>，债务问题给未来的政府提出了一个额外的问题，而这个问题还在酝酿之中。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 25 May 2023 10:29:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230525/finland-gets-flak-from-european-commission-for-skyrocketing-debt-1110577660.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230525/finland-gets-flak-from-european-commission-for-skyrocketing-debt-1110577660.html<category>经济</category><category>佩特里奥尔波</category><category>瓦尔迪斯·东布罗夫斯基斯</category><category>芬兰</category><category>德国</category><category>欧盟 (EU)</category><category>欧盟委员会</category><category>全国联合党 (芬兰)</category><category>债务</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Biden Taps US Air Force Chief Charles Brown to Chair Joint Chiefs of Staff]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110581264" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/12/1110441191_0:0:3071:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_f5c96d9e993433311c9078879b1dfa16.jpg?source-sid=afp" data-photoview-image-id="1110441173" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230525/biden-taps-us-air-force-chief-charles-brown-to-chair-joint-chiefs-of-staff-1110581264.html?share-img=1110441173"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / KIYOSHI OTA / 2023 年 5 月 18 日，在七国集团领导人峰会之前，美国总统拜登（左）在广岛与日本首相岸田文雄（未图示）进行双边会谈。 （摄影：Kiyoshi Ota / POOL / AFP）</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">美国总统乔·拜登（左）在七国集团领导人峰会之前于 2023 年 5 月 18 日在广岛举行的双边会议上与日本首相岸田文雄（未图示）会谈。 （摄影：太田清 / POOL / AFP）</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="afp" alt="US President Joe Biden (L) talks to Japan's Prime Minister Fumio Kishida (not pictured) during their bilateral meeting in Hiroshima on May 18, 2023, ahead of the G7 Leaders' Summit. (Photo by Kiyoshi Ota / POOL / AFP) - Sputnik In